HEADWORD: Institutional
<hw>In`sti*tu"tion*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Pertaining to, or treating of, an institution or institutions;
<as>as, <ex>institutional</ex> legends</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Institutional</qex> writers as Rousseau.</q> <rj><qau>J. S.
Mill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Instituted by authority.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Elementary; rudimental.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Institutionary</ent>⟦br⟧
